snippet.textDisplay: I'm sure it has been mentioned before, but if it hasn't - four things with the back seats. One, are there no individual A/C zones for each of the rear passengers? Dude, passenger vans have three-zone A/C. Two, the window shades for the tiny windows in the doors are really common in this type of cars. And since you mentioned the Lexus LS in the beginning, apart from not being vomit-inducing ugly like the G90, it one-ups the G90 - it has tiny windows in the C-pillars and those too have their individual tiny shades. Three - there are coat hooks in the rear grab handles above the windows as well, making this probably the only car I've seen with two coat hooks on each side of the rear passenger space. Four - is there really just one USB port for the rear seats in the armrest? Also, notice how the turn signal stalk is all aligned nicely when the headlight switch is on OFF. But you want the switch on AUTO all the time - and then it's not aligned. This is a problem I have with all the Hyundais. These are tiny details, but when you compete with the S class, you can't afford any mistakes.
snippet.textOriginal: I'm sure it has been mentioned before, but if it hasn't - four things with the back seats. One, are there no individual A/C zones for each of the rear passengers? Dude, passenger vans have three-zone A/C. Two, the window shades for the tiny windows in the doors are really common in this type of cars. And since you mentioned the Lexus LS in the beginning, apart from not being vomit-inducing ugly like the G90, it one-ups the G90 - it has tiny windows in the C-pillars and those too have their individual tiny shades. Three - there are coat hooks in the rear grab handles above the windows as well, making this probably the only car I've seen with two coat hooks on each side of the rear passenger space. Four - is there really just one USB port for the rear seats in the armrest? Also, notice how the turn signal stalk is all aligned nicely when the headlight switch is on OFF. But you want the switch on AUTO all the time - and then it's not aligned. This is a problem I have with all the Hyundais. These are tiny details, but when you compete with the S class, you can't afford any mistakes.
